        <briefdescription>
<para>Adds a callback to be executed asynchronously after each render frame. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This allows you to register a callback that will be called asynchronously after the offscreen rendering is complete for each frame. Unlike the synchronous version, this method does not block the render thread.</para>
<para>The callback receives a fence file descriptor that can be used to verify GPU rendering completion. The user is responsible for closing the file descriptor when it&apos;s no longer needed.</para>
<para>A callback of the following type should be used: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="keywordtype">void</highlight><highlight class="normal"><sp/>MyFunction(<ref refid="classDali_1_1OffscreenWindow_1a04e5da3c7f4640efa591c79949d7af71" kindref="member">OffscreenWindow</ref><sp/>window,<sp/>int32_t<sp/>fenceFd);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>fenceFd:<sp/>File<sp/>descriptor<sp/>for<sp/>the<sp/>fence<sp/>to<sp/>verify<sp/>GPU<sp/>rendering<sp/>completion</highlight><highlight class="normal"></highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal"></highlight><highlight class="comment">//<sp/>IMPORTANT:<sp/>User<sp/>must<sp/>call<sp/>close(fenceFd)<sp/>when<sp/>done<sp/>with<sp/>the<sp/>fence</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">callback</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Unique pointer to the callback base object to be executed post-render </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
